(17, 1, '2013-11-19 21:59:10', '2013-11-19 21:59:10', 'These are the two databases on which all the quantitative work in the book (econometrics, graphs, charts, etc) is based.Â  They contain essentially the same data, but formatted in version 1 for cross-sectional regressions, and in version 2 for panel regressions.Â  Both databases follow similar naming conventions, provided in the data key.\r\n\r\nThe data are organized by municipality and cover the period 1987-2007.Â  Financial variables are based on yearly observations, whereas most other variables (e.g. demographic, geographic, institutional) are based on data from the 1992 and 2001 censuses, and the unusual 1997 âMunicipal Censusâ of local infrastructure, service provision, and administrative processes.\r\n\r\nPlease note that the key grew out of my and my assistantsâ use of this data, and hence others are likely to find it somewhat cryptic.Â  The data require a bit more than the usual investment in familiarization, and are thus unsuitable for users looking to dip in quickly.Â  Further information and a huge amount of additional data are available on the Bolivian government websites listed under Useful Links.', 'Data', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'data', '', '', '2013-11-23 11:04:23', '2013-11-23 11:04:23', '', 0, 'http://governancefrombelow.net/?page_id=17', 0, 'page', '', 0),
